      "body" : "That method makes an assumption that the length of the matched part of the haystack will be the same number of UTF-16 code units as the length of the needle. So if you&#39;re searching for &quot;&#223;&quot; and the string contains &quot;SS&quot;, it won&#39;t find a match, even though these two strings are identical if you ignore the case (in German locale, and of course you do have to set the locale whenever doing this sort of thing.)"
